{"timestamp":"2026-02-13T03:15:04.266Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"item_completed","thread_id":"019c54f9-1b7e-7772-b04a-6448739fdd3e","turn_id":"019c54fa-c6ea-7470-b52d-7124c9826dca","item":{"type":"Plan","id":"019c54fa-c6ea-7470-b52d-7124c9826dca-plan","text":"# Plan: Restructure Note Pushing and Org Filtering\n\n## Summary\nRestructure note attachment and pushing so that org filtering gates all attachment paths, autopush consent/config is removed entirely, post-commit never pushes, and only the pre-push hook performs sync/push. Remove all credential overrides so git auth is inherited by hook-invoked commands. Update tests and CLI accordingly.\n\n## Public API / CLI Changes\n- Remove the `--push` flag from `cadence hydrate` and remove `push` from the `Hydrate` command variant.\n- Remove all user-facing “Auto-push” status output.\n\n## Implementation Steps\n\n### 1. Org filter gating for attachment\n- Add a repo-scoped org filter helper in `src/git.rs`:\n  - `fn repo_matches_org_filter(repo: &Path) -> Result<bool>` (or equivalent).\n  - Behavior:\n    - If `ai.cadence.org` is not set, return `true`.\n    - If set, resolve all remotes for the repo (using a new `remote_orgs_at(repo)` helper that runs `git -C <repo> remote` and `git -C <repo> remote get-url <name>`).\n    - Parse orgs via existing `parse_org_from_url`.\n    - Return `true` if any remote org matches (case-insensitive), otherwise `false`.\n    - If no remotes or no parseable orgs, return `false`.\n- Use this check to **gate attachment** in:\n  - `hook_post_commit_inner` (after `repo_root` is known, before any scanning/attachment).\n  - `retry_pending_for_repo` (once per repo before trying to attach).\n  - `run_hydrate` (per repo group, skip attachment for repos that don’t match).\n- Keep existing push-scoped org filter in `push::check_org_filter_remote` for remote-specific push decisions.\n\n### 2. Remove autopush consent/config\n- Delete `check_or_request_consent` and `should_push_remote_post_commit` from `src/push.rs`.\n- Update `should_push_remote` to only:\n  - Validate remote exists.\n  - Apply org filter for that remote.\n- Remove all `ai.cadence.autopush` reads/writes and related messages.\n- Remove the autopush section in `run_status` output.\n\n### 3. Push only from pre-push\n- Remove all push attempts outside the pre-push hook:\n  - Post-commit hook: remove `push::attempt_push_remote` calls.\n  - Retry flow: remove push attempts after successful attachment.\n  - Install flow: remove optional sync in install.\n  - Hydrate flow: remove push step entirely and remove `--push` option.\n- Keep pre-push hook behavior:\n  - `hook_pre_push_inner` continues to call `push::sync_notes_for_remote` when `should_push_remote(remote)` is true.\n\n### 4. Inherit Git auth in hooks\n- Remove all credential overrides from note fetch/merge/push commands:\n  - In `src/push.rs`, remove:\n    - `-c credential.helper=`\n    - `-c credential.interactive=never`\n    - `GIT_TERMINAL_PROMPT=0`\n    - `GIT_ASKPASS=echo`\n  - In `src/git.rs`, remove the same overrides from `push_notes`.\n- This ensures hooks use the user’s existing git auth setup and helpers.\n\n## Tests and Updates\n\n### Update/Remove Tests\n- `src/push.rs`:\n  - Remove tests for autopush consent.\n  - Update `should_push_remote` tests to not depend on `ai.cadence.autopush`.\n- `src/main.rs`:\n  - Remove tests asserting autopush status output.\n  - Update CLI parsing tests to remove `hydrate --push`.\n  - Update any tests expecting install-time sync/push or retry push behavior.\n- `src/git.rs`:\n  - Replace any tests that used `ai.cadence.autopush` for config helpers with another key (e.g., `ai.cadence.enabled`).\n\n### Add Tests\n- Add unit tests for the new repo org filter helper:\n  - No org filter set → allow.\n  - Org filter set, matching remote org → allow.\n  - Org filter set, non-matching remote org or no remotes → deny.\n  - Ensure it respects `GIT_CONFIG_GLOBAL` override in tests.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- No code path pushes notes except the pre-push hook.\n- No references to `ai.cadence.autopush` remain in code or tests.\n- Org filter gates all note attachment paths (post-commit, retry, hydrate).\n- Git commands in hooks inherit user auth (no forced `credential.helper=` or `GIT_ASKPASS`).\n- All tests pass and updated CLI/help output reflects new behavior.\n\n## Assumptions and Defaults\n- Org filter should deny attachment if no remotes or no matching org are found.\n- Removing `hydrate --push` is acceptable since pushing is now exclusively handled by pre-push.\n- Install should not perform any note sync/push.\n"}}}
