{"timestamp":"2026-02-13T03:16:46.442Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"agent_message","message":"Here’s what I found on inheriting Git auth in forked Git commands, and how it applies to this repo.\n\n**Findings (from Git docs):**\n- Git’s credential flow is: `GIT_ASKPASS` → `core.askPass` → `SSH_ASKPASS` → terminal prompt. If you set `GIT_ASKPASS` or `core.askPass`, you override the user’s normal auth flow. ([git-scm.com](https://git-scm.com/docs/gitcredentials/2.42.0?utm_source=openai))\n- Credential helpers are configured via `credential.helper`. If you pass `-c credential.helper=` (empty) you *reset* the helper list and prevent user-configured helpers (Keychain/GCM/etc.) from running. ([git-scm.com](https://git-scm.com/docs/gitcredentials/2.39.0?utm_source=openai))\n- Therefore, the best way to **inherit auth** is to **avoid overriding** these mechanisms in your spawned `git` commands and let Git use the user’s configured helpers/environment. ([git-scm.com](https://git-scm.com/docs/gitcredentials/2.42.0?utm_source=openai))\n\n**Practical guidance for this codebase:**\n- Remove all `-c credential.helper=` and `-c credential.interactive=never` overrides where we call `git fetch/merge/push`.\n- Remove any `GIT_ASKPASS` and `GIT_TERMINAL_PROMPT` overrides in those commands.\n- Keep the commands otherwise unchanged so they use the user’s normal credentials and helpers.\n\nThis aligns with “inherit auth” and is supported by how Git’s credential selection works. ([git-scm.com](https://git-scm.com/docs/gitcredentials/2.42.0?utm_source=openai))\n\n---\n\nYou also asked to keep `hydrate --push`. That conflicts with the earlier decision “push only from pre-push.” To make the plan decision-complete, I need to know which behavior you want.\n\nI’ll ask one precise question:\n\n**Which push rule should we adopt now that `hydrate --push` stays?**  \n(If you pick option 2 or 3, I’ll update the plan accordingly.)\n\n1. **Only pre-push (Recommended)** — keep `hydrate --push` but make it a no-op (warn or ignore).  \n2. **Explicit CLI pushes ok** — keep `hydrate --push` as a real push; remove automatic pushes from hooks/install/retry.  \n3. **Keep install sync too** — keep `hydrate --push` and install-time sync; remove post-commit/retry pushes.\n\nIf you answer, I’ll update the plan to match."}}
