{"timestamp":"2026-02-13T03:19:02.561Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"item_completed","thread_id":"019c54f9-1b7e-7772-b04a-6448739fdd3e","turn_id":"019c5501-deeb-71d3-bc14-216e6f67ed98","item":{"type":"Plan","id":"019c5501-deeb-71d3-bc14-216e6f67ed98-plan","text":"# Plan: Push Restructure + Org Filter Gating (Keep `hydrate --push`)\n\n## Summary\nUpdate push/attach behavior so org filtering gates all attachment paths, autopush config is removed entirely, only pre-push hook pushes automatically, and `hydrate --push` remains a CLI-triggered push. Remove all credential overrides so forked git commands inherit user auth.\n\n## Public API / CLI Changes\n- Keep `cadence hydrate --push` and keep the `push` flag in the `Hydrate` command variant.\n- Remove all user-facing “Auto-push” status output.\n\n## Implementation Steps\n\n### 1. Org filter gating for attachment\n- Add repo-scoped org filter helper in `src/git.rs`:\n  - `fn repo_matches_org_filter(repo: &Path) -> Result<bool>`.\n  - If `ai.cadence.org` is not set, return `true`.\n  - If set, gather all remotes for that repo (`remote_orgs_at(repo)`), parse orgs via `parse_org_from_url`, return `true` if any match (case-insensitive), else `false`.\n- Use this check to **gate attachment** in:\n  - `hook_post_commit_inner` (after repo root is known, before scanning/attachment).\n  - `retry_pending_for_repo` (once per repo before retry attachment).\n  - `run_hydrate` (per repo group; skip attach if not allowed).\n- Keep `push::check_org_filter_remote` for remote-specific push decisions.\n\n### 2. Remove autopush consent/config\n- Delete `check_or_request_consent` and `should_push_remote_post_commit` from `src/push.rs`.\n- Update `should_push_remote` to only check:\n  - Remote exists.\n  - Org filter for that remote matches.\n- Remove all `ai.cadence.autopush` reads/writes and related output.\n\n### 3. Push only from pre-push hook (plus explicit CLI push)\n- Remove all push attempts outside pre-push and explicit CLI:\n  - Post-commit hook: remove `push::attempt_push_remote` calls.\n  - Retry flow: remove push attempts after successful attachment.\n  - Install flow: remove optional sync during install.\n- Keep `hook_pre_push_inner` as the only hook that syncs/pushes.\n- Keep `hydrate --push` behavior:\n  - End of `run_hydrate` still calls `push::attempt_push_remote` (after org check passes).\n\n### 4. Inherit Git auth in forked commands\n- Remove all auth overrides in `src/push.rs` and `src/git.rs` for fetch/merge/push:\n  - Remove `-c credential.helper=`.\n  - Remove `-c credential.interactive=never`.\n  - Remove `GIT_TERMINAL_PROMPT` and `GIT_ASKPASS`.\n- This lets Git use the user’s configured credential helpers and askpass flow.\n\n## Tests and Updates\n\n### Update/Remove Tests\n- `src/push.rs`:\n  - Remove tests for autopush consent.\n  - Update `should_push_remote` tests to not depend on `ai.cadence.autopush`.\n- `src/main.rs`:\n  - Remove tests for autopush status output.\n  - Keep `hydrate --push` CLI parsing tests.\n  - Update any tests expecting post-commit/retry/install pushing.\n\n### Add Tests\n- Add unit tests for `repo_matches_org_filter`:\n  - No org filter set → allow.\n  - Org filter set, matching remote org → allow.\n  - Org filter set, no remotes or non-matching org → deny.\n  - Ensure tests isolate global config via `GIT_CONFIG_GLOBAL`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- Only pre-push hook does automatic sync/push.\n- `hydrate --push` still pushes when invoked explicitly.\n- No references to `ai.cadence.autopush` remain in code or tests.\n- Org filter gates all attachment paths (post-commit, retry, hydrate).\n- Forked git commands inherit user auth (no credential overrides).\n- Tests pass and CLI/help reflect new behavior.\n\n## Assumptions and Defaults\n- Org filter denies attachment if no remotes or no matching org are found.\n- Install no longer performs any push/sync.\n"}}}
{"timestamp":"2026-02-13T03:19:02.561Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"agent_message","message":"Here are the web findings on inheriting Git auth in forked Git commands, followed by an updated plan that keeps `hydrate --push` and restricts hook pushes to pre-push only.\n\n**Findings (Git auth inheritance)**\n- Git’s credential flow prefers `GIT_ASKPASS`, then `core.askPass`, then `SSH_ASKPASS`, then terminal prompt. Setting any of these (especially `GIT_ASKPASS`) changes the normal auth path. ([git-scm.com](https://git-scm.com/docs/gitcredentials.html?utm_source=openai))\n- `credential.helper` is the mechanism for user-configured credential storage; multiple helpers are tried in order. If `credential.helper` is set to the empty string, the helper list is reset to empty and user-configured helpers are skipped. ([git-scm.com](https://git-scm.com/docs/gitcredentials/2.35.0?utm_source=openai))\n- `credential.interactive=false` tells Git to avoid user interactivity; some helpers respect it. For “inherit user auth,” the best practice is to avoid overriding these settings and let Git use whatever the user already configured. ([git-scm.com](https://git-scm.com/docs/git-config/2.48.1?utm_source=openai))\n\n**Implication for this repo**\n- Remove all `-c credential.helper=`, `-c credential.interactive=never`, `GIT_TERMINAL_PROMPT`, and `GIT_ASKPASS` overrides in the forked `git` commands so hooks and CLI inherit the user’s auth configuration. ([git-scm.com](https://git-scm.com/docs/gitcredentials/2.35.0?utm_source=openai))\n\n---\n\n\nIf you want me to proceed with implementation, tell me to switch out of plan mode and I’ll start editing."}}
