{"timestamp":"2026-02-13T03:21:41.507Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"item_completed","thread_id":"019c54f9-1b7e-7772-b04a-6448739fdd3e","turn_id":"019c5504-1f66-7fb0-9594-626371c94b6a","item":{"type":"Plan","id":"019c5504-1f66-7fb0-9594-626371c94b6a-plan","text":"# Plan: Push Restructure + Org Filter Gating + Pre-Attach Fetch for Hydrate\n\n## Summary\nUpdate push/attach behavior so org filtering gates all attachment paths, autopush config is removed, only pre-push hook pushes automatically, `hydrate --push` remains a CLI-triggered push, and hydrate (including install) fetches/merges notes before attachment. Remove credential overrides so forked git commands inherit user auth.\n\n## Public API / CLI Changes\n- Keep `cadence hydrate --push` and keep the `push` flag in the `Hydrate` command variant.\n- Remove all user-facing “Auto-push” status output.\n\n## Implementation Steps\n\n### 1. Org filter gating for attachment\n- Add repo-scoped org filter helper in `src/git.rs`:\n  - `fn repo_matches_org_filter(repo: &Path) -> Result<bool>`.\n  - If `ai.cadence.org` is not set, return `true`.\n  - If set, gather all remotes for that repo (`remote_orgs_at(repo)`), parse orgs via `parse_org_from_url`, return `true` if any match (case-insensitive), else `false`.\n- Use this check to **gate attachment** in:\n  - `hook_post_commit_inner` (after repo root is known, before scanning/attachment).\n  - `retry_pending_for_repo` (once per repo before retry attachment).\n  - `run_hydrate` (per repo group; skip attach if not allowed).\n\n### 2. Remove autopush consent/config\n- Delete `check_or_request_consent` and `should_push_remote_post_commit` from `src/push.rs`.\n- Update `should_push_remote` to only check:\n  - Remote exists.\n  - Org filter for that remote matches.\n- Remove all `ai.cadence.autopush` reads/writes and related output.\n\n### 3. Push only from pre-push hook (plus explicit CLI push)\n- Remove all push attempts outside pre-push and explicit CLI:\n  - Post-commit hook: remove `push::attempt_push_remote` calls.\n  - Retry flow: remove push attempts after successful attachment.\n  - Install flow: remove optional sync during install.\n- Keep `hook_pre_push_inner` as the only hook that syncs/pushes.\n- Keep `hydrate --push` behavior:\n  - End of `run_hydrate` still calls `push::attempt_push_remote` when requested.\n\n### 4. Hydrate should fetch notes before attaching (covers install)\n- Add repo-scoped push-remote resolution helpers in `src/git.rs`:\n  - `resolve_push_remote_at(repo: &Path) -> Result<Option<String>>` (same rules as `resolve_push_remote`, but uses `git -C`).\n  - `remote_url_at(repo: &Path, remote: &str) -> Result<Option<String>>` (for org check on a repo path).\n- Add `push::fetch_merge_notes_for_remote(remote)` (or a `git`-level helper) that:\n  - Fetches `refs/notes/ai-sessions` from the remote into a temp ref.\n  - Merges that temp ref into local `refs/notes/ai-sessions`.\n  - Deletes the temp ref.\n  - Never pushes.\n  - Best-effort: logs on failure, does not abort hydrate.\n- In `run_hydrate`, before attaching for each repo group:\n  - If `repo_matches_org_filter(repo)` is false, skip entirely.\n  - If true, resolve the repo’s push remote; if found, fetch+merge notes **before** checking/attaching.\n  - If no remote, skip fetch and proceed with local notes only.\n- Install uses `run_hydrate`, so it inherits this behavior.\n\n### 5. Inherit Git auth in forked commands\n- Remove all auth overrides in `src/push.rs` and `src/git.rs` for fetch/merge/push:\n  - Remove `-c credential.helper=`.\n  - Remove `-c credential.interactive=never`.\n  - Remove `GIT_TERMINAL_PROMPT` and `GIT_ASKPASS`.\n- This lets Git use the user’s configured credential helpers and askpass flow.\n\n## Tests and Updates\n\n### Update/Remove Tests\n- `src/push.rs`:\n  - Remove tests for autopush consent.\n  - Update `should_push_remote` tests to not depend on `ai.cadence.autopush`.\n- `src/main.rs`:\n  - Remove tests for autopush status output.\n  - Keep `hydrate --push` CLI parsing tests.\n  - Update any tests expecting post-commit/retry/install pushing.\n\n### Add Tests\n- Unit tests for `repo_matches_org_filter` and `remote_orgs_at` (repo-scoped):\n  - No org filter set → allow.\n  - Org filter set, matching remote org → allow.\n  - Org filter set, no remotes or non-matching org → deny.\n  - Ensure tests isolate global config via `GIT_CONFIG_GLOBAL`.\n- Optional: a hydrate integration test that seeds an existing remote note, runs hydrate, and verifies it skips re-attaching due to pre-fetch merge.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- Only pre-push hook does automatic sync/push.\n- `hydrate --push` still pushes when invoked explicitly.\n- No references to `ai.cadence.autopush` remain in code or tests.\n- Org filter gates all attachment paths (post-commit, retry, hydrate).\n- Hydrate (and install) fetches/merges notes before attaching.\n- Forked git commands inherit user auth (no credential overrides).\n- Tests pass and CLI/help reflect new behavior.\n\n## Assumptions and Defaults\n- Org filter denies attachment if no remotes or no matching org are found.\n- If a repo has no push remote, hydrate proceeds without fetch.\n- Fetch/merge failures are logged and do not abort hydrate.\n"}}}
